constrains the curvature parameter to be -0.031 < $\Omega$k < 0.009 (95% CL), a level of precision comparable to that afforded by the current Type Ia SNe sample. Asserting a flat spatial geometry, we find that, in combination with WMAP, H 0 = 69.7+4.9-5.0 km s-1 Mpc-1 and w = -0.94+0.17-0.19 (68% CL), suggesting that the observations of B1608+656 constrain w as tightly as the current Baryon Acoustic Oscillation data do. {\textcopyright} 2010 The American Astronomical Society.},
